{"lemma":"رَدَّةٍ","slug":"رَدَّةٍ","root":"ر.د.د","root_slug":"ر-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15180","n15190","n15191"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"apostasy"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/rid.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15180","headword_ar":"رَدَّهُ","root":"rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~N","text_ar":"رَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marad~N","text_ar":"مَرَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroduwdN","text_ar":"مَرْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) this last an inf. n. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoluwfN","text_ar":"مَحْلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoquwlN","text_ar":"مَعْقُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rid~apN","text_ar":"رِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S [there said to be an inf. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~N","text_ar":"رَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rid~iydaY","text_ar":"رِدِّيدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K, [but in the S and L merely said to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~N","text_ar":"رَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) an intensive form, (Mgh, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarodaAdN","text_ar":"تَرْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is [also] an intensive or a frequentative inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, M, L,) and likewise an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rd~dhu","text_ar":"ردّدهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, S, M, L;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artd~hu","text_ar":"ارتدّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to return, go back, come back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revert; sent, turned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away; returned, rejected, repelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averted, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarafahu","text_ar":"صَرَفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEahu","text_ar":"دَفَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dfE","text_ar":"دفع"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano wajohihi","text_ar":"عَنْ وَجْهِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its, course"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M.) Hence, in the Kur [xxx. 42 and xlii. 46],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN laA marad~a lahu","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ لَا مَرَدَّ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day which there shall be no repelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averting"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning the day of resurrection. (Th, M, L.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoru A@ll~`hi laA marad~a lahu","text_ar":"اَمْرُ ا@للّٰهِ لَا مَرَدَّ لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The command of God, there is no repelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa liA^amori A@ll~`hi maroduwdN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِاَمْرِ ا@للّٰهِ مَرْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~N","text_ar":"رَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no repelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averting, the command of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A.) And"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1062},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu Eani AlA^amori","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ عَنِ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to return"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned him back"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away, with gentleness, from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~ahu","text_ar":"لَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, L.) ―         -b2-  Accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a","text_ar":"رَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made doubly trans. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the second objective complement when honour is intended to be shown, and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"when dishonour is intended; and they adduce as evidence of the correctness of their assertion the sayings in the Kur [xxviii. 12]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faradadonaAhu A_ilaY A^um~ihi","text_ar":"فَرَدَدْنَاهُ اـِلَى اُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"So we returned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restored, him to his mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and [iii. 142]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarud~uwkumo EalaY A^aEoqaAbikumo","text_ar":"يَرُدُّوكُمْ عَلَى اَعْقَابِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They will turn you back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cause you to return, to your former condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but instances may be found at variance with this assertion. (MF.) [Such instances are of frequent occurrence; though in others, the distinction pointed out above is observed, as may be seen in what here follows.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu A_ilaY manozilihi","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ اـِلَى مَنْزِلِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sent him back to his abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a A_ilayohi jawaAbFA","text_ar":"رَدَّ اـِلَيْهِ جَوَابًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered, to him a reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an answer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * L, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sent to him a reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an answer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Ealayohi","text_ar":"رَدَّ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He replied to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answered him, in an absolute sense;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) and also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by way of refutation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"objection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he replied against him;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaAla","text_ar":"فَقَالَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biqawolihi","text_ar":"بِقَوْلِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by his saying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA &c., passim.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Ealayohi Als~alaAma","text_ar":"رَدَّ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned to him the salutation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(The Trads. &c., passim.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Ealayohi AlwadiyEapa","text_ar":"رَدَّ عَلَيْهِ الوَدِيعَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned, rendered, restored,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sent"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him the deposite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaniyHapa","text_ar":"المَنِيحَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, lent to him for him to milk her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnH","text_ar":"منح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Ealayohi Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"رَدَّ عَلَيْهِ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~N","text_ar":"رَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marad~N","text_ar":"مَرَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rejected the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(such as a gift, A, and bad money, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refusing to receive it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accept it, from him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he cast it back at him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAd~ahu","text_ar":"رَادَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, K. *) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rejected the thing in reply to him, charging him with error in respect of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadotu Ealayohi qawolahu","text_ar":"رَدَدْتُ عَلَيْهِ قَوْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rebutted, rejected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repudiated, in reply to him, his saying, charging him with error therein; I refused him my assent to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, Msb.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadotu qawolahu","text_ar":"رَدَدْتُ قَوْلَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rebutted, rejected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repudiated, in reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"replication, his saying, as wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"erroneous; refuted it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refelled it; refused assent to it; controverted it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contradicted it."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a AlA^amora","text_ar":"رَدَّ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He refused assent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consent, to the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Ealayohi AlA^amora","text_ar":"رَدَّ عَلَيْهِ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He refused him his assent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consent, to the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Als~aAy^ila","text_ar":"رَدَّ السَّايِلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away, the beggar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asker, from the object of his want:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rebuffed him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sent away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dismissed, the beggar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asker, either with refusal"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a gift:"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in trads. with both of these meanings. (L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a AlbaAba","text_ar":"رَدَّ البَابَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closed, the door."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroduwdN","text_ar":"مَرْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a yadahu A_ilaY sayofihi","text_ar":"رَدَّ يَدَهُ اـِلَى سَيْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase of frequent occurrence, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put back his hand to his sword;"},{"kind":"text","text":"it being hung behind him: (see 4 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlf","text_ar":"خلف"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and hence, simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put his hand to his sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farad~uwA","text_ar":"فَرَدُّوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayodiyahumo fiY A^afowaAhihimo","text_ar":"اَيْدِيَهُمْ فِى اَفْوَاهِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xiv. 10, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they put their hands to their mouths"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of vehement anger or wrath or rage. (Jel.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu fiY A^amorK","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ فِى اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to enter again into an affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISh, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nks","text_ar":"نكس"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"رَدَّ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repeated the thing; did it again;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaAdahu","text_ar":"اَعَادَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewd","text_ar":"عود"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Ealayohimu","text_ar":"رَدَّ عَلَيْهِمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ayomaAna","text_ar":"الاَيْمَانَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repeated to them the oaths."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jld","text_ar":"جلد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [In this sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rid~iydaY","text_ar":"رِدِّيدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of the inf. ns. in use; as in the following ex.] It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA rid~iydaY fiY AlS~adaqapi","text_ar":"لَا رِدِّيدَى فِى الصَّدَقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no repeating in the case of the poor-rate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S, L;) meaning that the poor-rate shall not be taken twice (T, L) in one year. (L.) [See also 2, which has a similar signification.] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA laA yarud~u Ealayoka","text_ar":"هٰذَا لَا يَرُدُّ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yarud~u Ealayoka $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"لَا يَرُدُّ عَلَيْكَ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This will not return anything to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"], means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this will not bring any return to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this will not profit thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 483:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yarud~u Ealayoka h`*aA","text_ar":"مَا يَرُدُّ عَلَيْكَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This does not profit thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a A_ilayohi AlA^amora","text_ar":"رَدَّ اـِلَيْهِ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He referred the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"for management or decision: or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he committed to him the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faw~aDahu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"فَوَّضَهُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S and A and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwD","text_ar":"فوض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b9-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Al$~aYo'a A_ilaY A^aSolihi","text_ar":"رَدَّ الشَّىْءَ اـِلَى اَصْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase of frequent occurrence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reduced the thing to its original state."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a Alr~uboEa xumosFA","text_ar":"رَدَّ الرُّبْعَ خُمْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reduced the fourth part to a fifth part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbE","text_ar":"ربع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a A@ll~`hu nafosiY A_ilaY waqoti A@notihaA='i mud~atiY","text_ar":"رَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ نَفْسِى اـِلَى وَقْتِ ا@نْتِهَا=ءِ مُدَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God brought my soul to the time of the end of my duration"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IB, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr","text_ar":"امر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu A_ilaY AlA^amori","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ اـِلَى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reduced him to the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSr","text_ar":"قصر"},{"kind":"text","text":", in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSarahu EalaY","text_ar":"قَصَرَهُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he appropriated him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, restrictively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK in that art.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a A=xira Al$~aYo'i A_ilaY A^aw~alihi","text_ar":"رَدَّ ا=خِرَ الشَّىْءِ اـِلَى اَوَّلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eks","text_ar":"عكس"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a A^aw~alahu EalaY A=xirihi","text_ar":"رَدَّ اَوَّلَهُ عَلَى ا=خِرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb in the same art., &c.,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reversed the thing; made the last part of it to be first,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first part of it to be last; turned it hind part before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part behind."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~a baEoDa AlA^amori EalaY baEoDi","text_ar":"رَدَّ بَعْضَ الاَمْرِ عَلَى بَعْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reversed the order of part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the parts, of the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rk","text_ar":"رك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadotu Ealayohi A^amorahu","text_ar":"رَدَدْتُ عَلَيْهِ اَمْرَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakasotuhu Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَكَسْتُهُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I reversed to him his affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case; I made his affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, to become the contrary of what it was to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eks","text_ar":"عكس"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a radadonaA lakumu Alkar~apa Ealayohimo","text_ar":"ثُمَّ رَدَدْنَا لَكُمُ الكَرَّةَ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xvii. 6, means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then we gave to you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the turn to prevail against them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the victory over them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) ―         -b13-  [Hence, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, rendered him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to become;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~arahu","text_ar":"صَيَّرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) when it has a second objective complement the contrary in meaning to the first; as in the following ex.; and it may have this meaning likewise when it has a second objective complement differing in meaning from the first in a less degree.] A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"ramaY AlHadavaAnu nisowapa A=li HarobK\n                      \n                     \n                        biA^amorK qado samadona lahu sumuwdaA\n                      \n                     \n                        farad~a $uEuwrahun~a Als~uwda biyDFA\n                      \n                     \n                        warad~a wujuwhahun~a AlbiyDa suwdaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The casualties of fortune smote the women of the family of Harb with an event whereat they became confounded with great confoundedness; and it rendered their black hairs white, and rendered their white faces black"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smd","text_ar":"سمد"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","L","K","Mgh","TA","Sb","Msb","A","T"]},{"entry_id":"n15190","headword_ar":"رَدَّةٌ","root":"rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, A, K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rd~apN","text_ar":"ردَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a copy of the M,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quality that repels the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unseemliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, IDrd, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with somewhat of comeliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the face: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat of unseemliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A) in the face of a woman who has some comeliness, (T,) or in the face of a comely woman: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unseemliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugliness, from which the eye reverts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Leylà:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, IDrd, M,) in a man, (IAar,) or in the face. (IDrd, M.) ―         -b2-  And the former, (accord. to a copy of the M,) or ↓ the latter, (A, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A receding"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaAEasN","text_ar":"تَقَاعَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the chin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when there is in the face somewhat of unseemliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugliness, and somewhat of comeliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b3-  And the former, (accord. to a copy of the A,) or ↓ the latter, (K,) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned sound of"},{"kind":"text","text":"the echo; as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEotu rad~apa AlS~adaY","text_ar":"سَمِعْتُ رَدَّةَ الصَّدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I heard the returned sound of the echo"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"echo of a mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  Also the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stipend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaTiy~apN","text_ar":"عَطِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, from a trad.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Affection, and desire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the phrase,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1064},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu rad~apN fiynaA","text_ar":"لَهُ رَدَّةٌ فِينَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has affection, and desire, for us"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in a verse of 'Orweh Ibn-El-Ward. (Sh.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","A","K","IAar","IDrd","M"]},{"entry_id":"n15191","headword_ar":"رِدَّةٌ","root":"rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airotad~a","text_ar":"اِرْتَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K,) signifying ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An apostacy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a returning from El-Islám to unbelief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rid~apN Eani AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"رِدَّةٌ عَنِ الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~apN","text_ar":"رَدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b3-  Also Camels'"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking water a second time"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and so causing the milk to return into their udders;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadN","text_ar":"رَدَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, L.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A swelling of the teats of a she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their swelling by reason of the collecting of the milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadN","text_ar":"رَدَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in either sense: and the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a camel's udder's becoming shining, and infused with milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"udder's becoming filled with milk before bringing forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A remain, remainder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything remaining."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","L","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}